The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 22 August is 64,708 (7,458 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 17 August, there were 2,545 new confirmed cases (293.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 10 August, there were 2,558 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 1% (13 fewer cases).
